{
  "texts": [
    "Here, W 0 is frozen, while B and A are initialised randomly and updated during fine-tuning.",
    "The decomposition is scaled by hyperparameter α and rank r, thus giving the new expression in Eq 2.",
    "Once the fine-tuning stage has been completed, the additional matrices can be removed by simplifying W 0, A and B to a single matrix W 0 0, thus giving the same number of parameters as the original pre-trained model.",
    "This solves the problem of increased inference time.",
    "When performing hyperparameter search, the α hyperparameter can be fixed since it is proportional to the learning rate [20]."
  ]
}